      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn45.166:1.1",
          "pli": "“Tayome, bhikkhave, khilā. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, there are these three kinds of barrenness. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.166:1.2",
          "pli": "Katame tayo? ",
          "en": "What three? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.166:1.3",
          "pli": "Rāgo khilo, doso khilo, moho khilo—",
          "en": "Greed, hate, and delusion. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.166:1.4",
          "pli": "ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo khilā. ",
          "en": "These are the three kinds of barrenness. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.166:1.5",
          "pli": "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇannaṃ khilānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya … pe … ayaṃ ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvetabbo”ti. ",
          "en": "The noble eightfold path should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these three kinds of barrenness.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn45.166:1.6",
          "pli": "Chaṭṭhaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
